title: Print, "Engraving: Monograms of two letters", ca. 1765
inscribed: Lower left: "Langlois exe. cum privil. reg."
creditline: Gift of Eleanor and Sarah Hewitt
description: Vertical rectangle. Fifteen monograms in five rows. The letters are composed of leaf scrolls. They are two letter monograms in alphabetical order starting with AS and ending with Bm.
